      <section name='oldlady'>

         <para number='1' comment='Feed birds - 2342 - no coin'>
         The old lady will only sell you the bird food if you have a coin or token to give her - which you do not. She is old-fashioned and is not interested in groats transferred direct from your bank balance. How eccentric!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Got coin so feed birds - player'>
         You hand your 7-groat coin to the old lady and in return she gives you a bag of bird seed. You start to scatter it around, and the alert pigeons soon start to crowd around you and peck it up. One brave bird hops onto your arm and starts to eat the seed directly out of the bag; luckily it flies off again before making a mess of your clothes! Before long, the birds have eaten all of the food, and they fly off to bother somebody else.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='roomex'>
         A crowd of pigeons starts to crowd around %s, who is scattering bird seed around. The hungry birds peck it up.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         One brave bird hops onto %s's arm and starts to eat the seed directly out of the bag!
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Got token - feed birds - player'>
         You hand your 13-groat piece to the old lady and in return she gives you two bags of bird seed which you scatter around. Soon you are surrounding by greedy pigeons, who peck up the seed. Some even land on parts of your body, including your head, but once they have eaten all the food they fly off to bother somebody else.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='roomex'>
         A crowd of pigeons starts to crowd around %s, who is scattering bird seed around. The hungry birds peck it up.
         </para>

         <para number='7'>
         One of the birds even lands on %s's head - how very unhygienic!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='pendant'>

         <para number='1' comment='Twirl pendant - player'>
         You hold the pendant out in front of you and twirl it round in a circle. Light flashes from the prism, sending rainbows all around the room.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='roomex'>
         Flashes of colored light suddenly appear, as %s twirls a prism and sends rainbows all around the room.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Wear pendant'>
         You put the pendant around your neck and admire the way the prism hangs down. Unfortunately, as you take your hands off the chain, the clasp snaps and the pendant falls to the ground. The prism shatters and the chain rolls away out of sight.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='Put pendant in slot 2215 - no'>
         You are not carrying a pendant.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Got pendant - player'>
         You insert the pendant into the slot, but it it doesn't fit very well. Giving it a shove, you insert it as far as it will go, until it is stuck fast. A red warning light begins to flash, and an alarm buzzes loudly. Everybody in the exchange looks at you to see what you have done.
         </para>

         <para number='6'>
         A repair technician appears and glares at you. "Another fool trying to put strange items in the slot machine," he mutters to himself, as he uses some kind of tool to remove the pendant you mistakenly tried to insert. He resets the machine, which shuts off the alarm, then walks off, still grumbling, and taking your pendant with him.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='roomex'>
         You hear the sudden buzz of an alarm, and see a red warning light flashing on and off. Looking around for the cause, you notice that %s is looking embarrassed.
         </para>

         <para number='8'>
         A repair technician appears and you see him glaring at %s. He mutters to himself, "Another fool trying to put strange items in the slot machine," as he uses some kind of tool to remove whatever was mistakenly inserted. He resets the machine, which shuts off the alarm, then walks off, still grumbling.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='Drop pendant - not in loc 2410'>
         You drop the pendant and it falls to the ground. The prism shatters and the chain rolls away out of sight.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='In 2410'>
         You drop the pendant on the altar. The pilgrim stands up and shimmers, transforming into the Goddess of Rainbows herself. She smiles and says, "Let the planet administrator know that you ahve crossed the crystal bridge and she will arrange for your name to join the list of others who have completed the journey." She shimmers again briefly and appears once again to be a humble pilgrim.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='Give pendant'>
         You have not said who you want to give the pendant to.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='pilgrim'>

         <para number='1' comment='Give pendant to pilgrim 2410 no'>
         You are not carrying a pendant.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Got pendant so hand it over'>
         You offer the pendant to the pilgrim, who then stands up and shimmers, transforming into the Goddess of Rainbows herself. She smiles and says, "Thank you for bringing this to me. It shows you have the wit and wisdom to do what is necessary." She removes the prism from its chain and folds your hand over it telling you that you will need it elsewhere.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='continuation of pilgrim speech'>
         "There are other missions that need solving before you are finished," she says softly. You try to speak with her to get more information about these "other missions" but she does not respond, only smiles one more time before shimmering and becoming once again, the humble pilgrim.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='sandal'>

         <para number='1' comment='Get sandal - 2468 - already got'>
         You are already carrying a sandal - which is trying its best to escape - and you cannot handle another one at the same time.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Take a sandal'>
         You try to pick up a sandal.  One of them skitters across the floor, its wings beating frantically. With a swift lunge, you manage to catch it.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Drop sandal'>
         You let go of the sandal and it flies off out of sight.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='Wear sandal - player'>
         You put the sandal on, and you are pulled into the air unceremoniously by one foot as the sandal tries to fly off. After dangling by your ankle (or equivalent) for a few moments, the leather strap breaks and the sandal flies out of sight.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Wear sandal - roomex'>
         You hear a sudden squeal, as %s is pulled unceremoniously into the air by one foot - the cause seems to be a winged sandal. After dangling by the ankle (or equivalent) for a few moments, the leather strap breaks and the sandal flies out of sight.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Throw sandal - player'>
         You chuck the sandal as hard as you can. It flaps its wings, obviously intending to fly away, but the angle at which you threw it sends it around in an arc so that it returns to your hand like a boomerang.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Throw sandal - roomex'>
         You hear a whirring noise, caused by %s chucking a sandal across the room. It flaps its wings, obviously intending to fly away, but the angle at which it was thrown sends it around in an arc so that it returns like a boomerang.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='Give sandal'>
